pect copy flow to clarify with it.\n- Keep local price regime + bias as the primary lens for overnight research.\n\n**Next:** If another late session shows the same divergence, compare whether copy-flow clarity ever improves during the next active-day windows. If it never does, that\u2019s strong evidence it should remain permanently secondary.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-22 03:15 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] 03h Stayed Structurally Active While Copy Flow Collapsed Into Pure Expiry Noise\n\n**Task:** Determine whether the emerging 03h tape is still structurally interesting and whether PM copy flow becomes more or less informative as the overnight session ages.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains out of active hours.\n- 03h is still structurally active, not dead:\n  - **15** tracked windows so far\n  - price regimes split evenly across three states:\n    - `(0.495, 0.505)` \u2192 **5**\n    - `(0.505, 0.495)` \u2192 **5**\n    - `(0.465, 0.535)` \u2192 **5**\n  - **8** windows reached `|bias| >= 45`\n  - **5** reached `|bias| >= 55`\n  - max bias = **69.2**\n  - regime flips observed: **2**\n- So 03h",
